column1: # Information for SNPs genotyped in LG/J x SM/J mouse advanced
# intercross line. Each row refers to a single SNP. All SNP
# information and genomic positions are based on Mouse Genome Assembly
# The columns of the table are:
#  (1) id (a unique label assigned to each SNP)
#  (3) genetic distance (in cM) estimated from reference panel
#      (refer to the Mouse Map Converter from the Center for
#  (6) genetic distance (in cM) estimated using mice from F33 and
#      F34 generations in the advanced intercross line
# Note that some SNPs do not match with a corresponding SNP in the
# genetic distance from the reference panel by looking up the base
# pair position of the SNP. There is one SNP (rs33886947) that could
# not be located by the Mouse Map Converter
# distance estimate is based on base pair position
# rs31528753 was incorrectly labeled as rs31528785 in the original
# data (it must have been a typing error). SNP 1-191513527 was
# recorded with a nonsense position (1.93e14) and so it was removed.
